ActCannabis Act
SubjectCannabis Act (Police Enforcement) Regulations
PrecisCANNABIS ACT (POLICE ENFORCEMENT) REGULATIONS in order to ensure that law enforcement will continue to be exempt from criminal prosecution when carrying out activities as part of investigations that are otherwise proscribed by the Cannabis Act as criminal offences, as has been provided for under the Controlled Drugs and Substances Act Regulations; as well as, extend the exemptions to military police as authorized by section 139(6) of the Cannabis Act.
